---
// raphaelfakhri.com - personal site. Who he is, what he believes. Nothing for sale.
// Built with Astro, output to ./dist. One tiny script: a version-poller that live-reloads
// the page when a new build deploys, so edits appear without a manual refresh.
const BUILD_ID = process.env.BUILD_ID || process.env.GITHUB_SHA || 'dev';
const links = [
  { href: 'https://x.com/raphaelfakhri00', label: 'X' },
  { href: 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/raphaelfakhri', label: 'LinkedIn' },
  { href: 'https://www.youtube.com/@RaphaelFakhri00', label: 'YouTube' },
  { href: 'https://raphaelfakhri.substack.com', label: 'Newsletter' },
];

const values = [
  {
    title: 'Build with people who push you, not people who please you',
    body: 'Liking each other isn&rsquo;t the mechanism; pressure is. Friendship is fuel, not the product. Adam Smith wrote about what strangers achieve together. Newton and Leibniz hated each other and still gave us calculus. Jobs was hard to like and hard to beat. I&rsquo;d rather be sharpened than comforted.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Take the hard road on purpose',
    body: 'Choose the thing that costs you something. That&rsquo;s where you actually grow. Amor fati: don&rsquo;t just accept the cost, want it. The easy road is usually a longer way to a smaller life.',
  },
  {
    title: 'A value is only real if it sometimes costs you',
    body: 'Everything else is a story you tell after the fact. Choose, don&rsquo;t justify. Hold me to it.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Value belongs to whoever creates it',
    body: 'Not to whoever&rsquo;s best positioned to extract it. No rent-seeking, no lock-in. If the only reason something is yours is that someone can&rsquo;t leave, it was never yours.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Win only when the other person wins',
    body: 'And still charge like the work is worth it. Generous, not self-erasing. A deal where I lose isn&rsquo;t generosity; it&rsquo;s a subsidy. A deal where you lose isn&rsquo;t a win; it&rsquo;s a debt that comes due.',
  },
  {
    title: 'The Raphael choice',
    body: 'Spend your life to minimize regret, boredom, and misery. Take the cheapest path that&rsquo;s still genuinely interesting. Do more with less.',
  },
];
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>Raphael Fakhri</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Raphael Fakhri. What I believe, written down so I can be held to it." />
  <link rel="icon" href={"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 100 100'%3E%3Ctext y='.9em' font-size='90'%3E%F0%9F%98%8E%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E"} />
  <meta property="og:title" content="Raphael Fakhri" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="What I believe, written down so I can be held to it." />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://raphaelfakhri.com" />
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <p><strong>Raphael Fakhri</strong></p>
  </header>

  <hr />

  <main>
    <h1>I&rsquo;m Raphael. And so what?</h1>
    <p>I&rsquo;m Lebanese. I&rsquo;m not really a developer anymore. Nobody is. We don&rsquo;t build software now; we talk to AI. What&rsquo;s left that&rsquo;s actually mine is what I believe. So that&rsquo;s what this page is: a short list I live by, not a long one I perform.</p>
    <p>What I want is simple. Learn business. Make good decisions. Find the bottleneck and lift it with whatever tool I&rsquo;ve got, and if AI is the tool, I use AI. Spin up businesses fast; see the opportunity and grab it before anyone else. I don&rsquo;t need to be well known. I want to be useful.</p>
    <p>I think long and hard before I solve anything. I want the problem dissected from every angle. I&rsquo;ll spend more time understanding it than solving it.</p>

    <hr />

    <section id="mission">
      <h2>What I want you to get</h2>
      <p>Find your real bottleneck, and use the right tool to lift it. That&rsquo;s the whole game. AI isn&rsquo;t the right tool for everything. It&rsquo;s the right tool when your own time is the bottleneck. The clearest case: you&rsquo;re answering the same questions over and over, acting like a human decision tree. That&rsquo;s not work; it&rsquo;s a machine&rsquo;s job. Hand it to AI and buy your time back. But a glass factory drowning in orders doesn&rsquo;t need AI; it needs price or capacity. Most people don&rsquo;t need more software. They need to find the one thing holding them back, and move it.</p>
    </section>

    <hr />

    <section id="demo">
      <h2>Prompt and wait</h2>
      <p>Where I think work is going: you name the goal, agents recurse until it&rsquo;s done. Here&rsquo;s one making you a burger.</p>
      <div id="flow"></div>
      <p>That is not science fiction. It is the thing we already have, pointed at a longer horizon and given the ability to call itself. The loop is the whole trick: keep going until the goal is met.</p>
      <p>What it does to scarcity is the interesting part. If any goal can be filled at close to zero cost and the only input left is patience, then scarcity of stuff is basically solved. That is abundance, on the supply side. The honest catch is who owns the fleets. Making things free is a technology problem. Sharing them is not.</p>
      <p>And here is the part that matters. When production gets cheap, the scarce thing moves. Solve making, and the bottleneck jumps to time, or attention, or knowing what to even ask for. So the skill that survives every version of this is the same one: find the thing actually holding the goal back, and move it. Right now, for me, it is that not enough people know I exist. So I wrote this.</p>
    </section>
    <style is:global>
      #demo #flow { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace; line-height: 1.9; margin-top: .5rem; min-height: 11em; }
      #demo #flow .step { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(6px); transition: opacity .35s ease, transform .35s ease; }
      #demo #flow .step.on { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
      #demo #flow .step .a { color: #2e936f; font-weight: 600; }
    </style>
    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        var flow = document.getElementById('flow');
        if (!flow) return;
        var steps = [
          { d: 0, h: '🧑 you', t: '“make me a burger”' },
          { d: 1, h: '🤖 agent', t: 'check the kitchen… no patties' },
          { d: 2, h: '🚚 sub-agent', t: 'spin up a beef fleet' },
          { d: 3, h: '🐄 fleet', t: 'raise cattle → grind patties ✓' },
          { d: 1, h: '🤖 agent', t: 'assemble the burger' },
          { d: 0, h: '🍔 done', t: 'delivered, you just waited' }
        ];
        var nodes = steps.map(function (s) {
          var el = document.createElement('div');
          el.className = 'step';
          el.style.paddingLeft = (s.d * 1.6) + 'em';
          el.innerHTML = (s.d ? '↳ ' : '') + '<span class="a">' + s.h + ':</span> ' + s.t;
          flow.appendChild(el);
          return el;
        });
        var i = 0;
        function tick() {
          if (i < nodes.length) { nodes[i].classList.add('on'); i++; setTimeout(tick, 850); }
          else { setTimeout(function () { nodes.forEach(function (n) { n.classList.remove('on'); }); i = 0; setTimeout(tick, 500); }, 2600); }
        }
        tick();
      })();
    </script>

    <hr />

    <section id="find">
      <h2>Where to find me</h2>
      <ul>
        {links.map((l) => (
          <li><a href={l.href}>{l.label}</a></li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

  <hr />

  <footer>
    <p>&copy; Raphael Fakhri. Scarcity is a technology problem.</p>
  </footer>
  <script define:vars={{ BUILD_ID }}>
    // Live-reload: poll the build id and reload when a new version is deployed.
    setInterval(async () => {
      try {
        const r = await fetch('/version.json?cb=' + Date.now(), { cache: 'no-store' });
        if (!r.ok) return;
        const { id } = await r.json();
        // Reload only on a strictly newer build (ids are timestamps); ignore stale reads.
        if (id && Number(id) > Number(BUILD_ID)) location.reload();
      } catch {}
    }, 3000);
  </script>
</body>
</html>
